data.text:
Full Name: William James Murray

Profession: Actor and Comedian

Biography: First gained exposure on "Saturday Night Live" for which he earned an Emmy Award and later went on to star in numerous comedy films, including "Ghostbusters", "Caddyshack", and "Groundhog Day".

Murray also starred in the critically acclaimed "Lost in Translation" earning him a Golden Globe, a BAFTA and an Oscar nomination for Best Actor.

Born: September 21, 1950

Birthplace: Evanston, Illinois, USA

Age: 73 years old
